# TypeScript Style

- Strict mode, no `any` — use `unknown` + narrowing or a zod schema instead.
- Prefer explicit return types on exported functions, especially in `src/lib`.
- No default exports except Next.js special files (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`,
  `route.ts`) which require them.
- Small, single-purpose modules over large multi-export files — this matters
  especially in `src/lib/sources/*` where isolation is a correctness requirement,
  not just style.
- Don't add abstraction (generic source interfaces, plugin registries) ahead of
  need — three concrete sources exist before any "source framework" is justified.
  Propose it, don't just build it.
